Class SharedInteger

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.analysis.GenericObject
      • com.cafean.client.analysis.AbstractComponent
        • com.cafean.client.analysis.AbstractBeanComponent
          • com.cafean.client.values.components.AbstractSharedValue

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CloneableBlock, PibBlock, Checkable, ComponentElement, IdentHolder, ModelElement, DecoratedBean, PropertyController, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.undo.StateEditable
    public class SharedInteger
extends AbstractSharedValue
implements PibBlock, CloneableBlock, PropertyController, DecoratedBean
    A user-defined integer; instances of which may represent either scalar values or enumerations. These values may be referenced by CIntegers and accessed by user-defined functions. Furthermore, the value may be parametric, which allows defining multiple values in place of the integer reference.

        public int getValue()
        Returns the value of this shared integer. This value is one of the following:
        • If in enumeration mode, the value of the currently selected enumeration entry is returned.
        • If in scalar mode, the local value is returned. This value may have been set by the user, a function, etc.

        public java.lang.String getCurrentValue​(int modelUnits)
        Returns the current parametric value as a String. When the shared value is set to incremental, this returns the product of the current index and increment added to the start value. Otherwise, it returns the value in the parametric array at the current index.
